The paper discusses the kinematic analysis and trajectory planning of a 5-axis parallel kinematic machine, which falls under the field of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also mentions the use of a control loop and the need for high frequency computation, which could be related to control systems (cs.SY). The Orthoglide 5-axis is a mechanical system, so it could also be categorized under mechanical engineering (cs.ME). The paper includes examples of joint angles, velocities, and accelerations, which could be related to computer vision (cs.CV) if the data is being analyzed or processed visually. Finally, the paper could also be categorized under robotics and automation (cs.ROB) due to its focus on a specific type of robot.
